description: The Temple of Concord, located in the so-called "Valle dei Templi" of Agrigento, dates ca. 440-430 B.C.
details: The temple measures 39.44 x 16.91 m (129.4 ft Ã— 55.5 ft) and has a six by thirteen column ground plan. The structure is extremely well preserved.
